reviews.review_text:
06-12-76-Everything you gather Wow,  a vintage FM broadcast sparkly shiny and new.
Essential 1976-A BOLT of inspiration!
Track #13- interview is a great listen.

------ post script
If I understand the rules
this is downloadable
quality of this is better than many
above average soundboards.
You know the 1 to 5 star system is what we got
but a show like this really captures the band live.
If you grade on musical prowess
yes, there are some errors
both from the band 
and even some warts in the recording
but if you compare this recording quality wise
to others from 1976 this is super sweet.
I do learn from reviewers who are able
to point out details that I tend to be oblivious too
such as comparing versions of tunes
giving historical  and researched background details
and I will be the 1st to admit that by giving out 5 stars regularly 
it makes it hard to differentiate.
So my standard is do I dig the show?
For me to get into the show it has to have listenable sound.
I went to a few shows where the sound was off
usually because of my location
and truthfully I don't ever want to replicate that experience.
My honest feeling is that almost every show I was able to attend was really good. 1984-1993 (less so for me after 92)
Also I went to many a rock n roll concert and with a very few exceptions 
It was always The Dead that were playing exactly what i wanted to hear. (or at least there was always endless potential for the same)

I keep telling myself to get up and dance more
but alas them bones don't shake rattle and roll
so regularly anymore.
Anyway, i am dancing in my mind
and that is a very good thing.
In Summary:
Thank GOD for the Grateful Dead.
